author: @jungoohappiness
text: What kind of free hate is this that Jaehyun has been receiving in recent months due to a deduction from "fans", or rather, from people who have nothing to do? Anyone who's been in kpop for years knows that what's most there is theory and ship pulled out of the ass to link one artist to another, in a relationship or anything like that, but there are times when this goes beyond the limit. Doing all this cause of the name of a song (which is the most generic, not even specific) is fucked up and even worse is going to hate the guy without having any proof of anything, especially cause all the rumors are from fandom and there is no evidence, just like they spent years saying that this R was dating Suzy and to this day no one knows and just like they hated Jaden Smith when she released that bomb in the form of an album. I exaggerated the text cause this type of thing has been irritating me for a while now, even though I have been in the hallyu world for almost 8 years.

author: @periz3057
text: Ogni volta che ascolto la tua voce, è come un fuoco che mi avvolge. La passione che trasmetti in ogni nota è travolgente, come se cantassi direttamente all'anima. Il tuo talento non è solo musicale, è un'esperienza sensoriale completa: quel mix di carisma, sguardi intensi e movenze ipnotiche rende impossibile distogliere lo sguardo. Sei una tempesta di emozioni, capace di far vibrare ogni fibra del mio essere. Ogni canzone è una promessa sussurrata, ogni verso un brivido che corre lungo la pelle. Non canti, seduci. Non interpreti, vivi ogni parola con un’intensità che lascia senza fiato. Sei l’essenza della passione trasformata in melodia. Con te non è mai solo musica, è un viaggio che incendia l’anima. Sei pura arte viva.

author: @annalog-hs4ch
text: This is my most favourite song on the album. There's a lot to say about this song, not only the catchy melody, the addictive Jaehyun's voice and vibe, but also the story behind it. I'm an imaginative person, and I feel like this is the next chapter after Favourite - NCT 127, Lost and Forever Only. I don't know why but Jaehyun keeps giving me the vibe of a vampire guy, who has a tragic love with the one that he can't never have, he is the one who best represents the Favourite story. Coming to the second chapter - 'Lost', the period when he drowned his life in pain and solitude with the incessant nostalgia for the one he loved. In 'Forever Only' chapter, this is the time when he gave up his hopeless nostalgia, he decided to just reminisce the girl in mind and heart. And now after many years, 'Roses' here to represents his chaotic feelings: anger, animus, disappointment, despair, deep sorrow... Its was all the reasonable emotions to express the merciless truth of not having his love. The rose is also some kind of symbolic image that reminds Jaehyun of the girl, I believe. That's all I can say. That's all I want to say about this song, cause I believe a beautiful song like this deserves a comment like this, too.

author: @Pedi62
text:
“Since I first heard Roses, I've felt that the upcoming album is going to be very genuine. The emotions you convey through the melodies, the lyrics, and your expressions in the MV don't give off that feeling of, "Oh, this is the song the company picked for you," or "You were told to act like this or that in this part." Of course, I don't want to idealize everything. I'm well aware that many musicians or PDs or experts were involved in the production of your album. But thankfully, their contributions have only enhanced your unique colors. It's something I’m soooo grateful for.

I don't know if this is too much to ask, but I hope that the emotions you pour into the love songs you sing come, at least in part, from real experiences outside of the spotlight. Your career doesn't allow you the time or freedom for dating, but I still hope you've found a way to sneak through a small gap, allowing this beautiful feeling to reach your heart. Jaehyun, you have such a warm heart and eyes filled with love for everything— someone like that deserves to love and be loved.

To me, Smoke feels like the first page of a book our Jaehyunie is eager to write. Beyond being NCT 127 member and having that well-known perfectly sculpted appearance, it seems like you want to show the world that you can be even bolder and capable to conquer so much more. So, I'm really excited to see what's next because, honestly, your potential is limitless.”

Actually I intended to write this down and keep it to myself, but after watching Lee Mujin Service, I felt the urge to share it somewhere. Who knows, maybe one magical day, Jaehyun will find comfort from what I felt, just as I always find comfort from his music.
